      <section id="how" class="section">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>How it works</h2>
          <div class="two-col">
            <div>
              <ol class="steps">
                <li><strong>Deploy</strong> on a small VPS with Docker.</li>
                <li><strong>Build</strong> and present in the browser (no desktop app).</li>
                <li><strong>Publish</strong> as a link, embed it, or export when you need to share.</li>
              </ol>
              <p class="fineprint">
                Operational promise: data lives on disk (JSON + uploads) so backups and restores are predictable—and you
                keep control of where it lives.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <pre class="code"><code># Local (dev)
npm install
npm run start

# VPS (typical)
docker compose up -d</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
